com.clrs

Interface Algorithm


  • public interface Algorithm
    This interface is used to enforce some methods that every algorithm of the CLRS textbook *must* implement.

    Some common methods are to retrieve complexities and instances which cause worst case behavior.

    • Method Detail

      • getName

        String getName()
        Gets the name of the algorithm.
        Returns:
        The name of the algorithm.

      • getInfo

        String getInfo()
        Gets some wiki about the algorithm.

        The wiki can include information extracted from Wikipedia and other sources.

        The String is already properly formatted and be embedded in a print statement to display it.

        For example System.out.println(<Algorithm>.getInfo());

        Returns:
        Information about the algorithm.
        See Also:
        getComplexity()

      • getComplexity

        String getComplexity()
        Gets the time complexity of the algorithm.

        As with getInfo(), the format of the time complexity is already in a table form and can be embedded in a print statement to display it.

        For example System.out.println(<Algorithm>.getComplexity());

        Returns:
        Various complexities of the algorithm.

      • getExampleBest

        String getExampleBest()
        Returns a best case example(s) for the algorithm (if known).

        As with getInfo(), the String is already properly formatted and can be embedded in a print statement to display it.

        For example System.out.println(<Algorithm>.getExampleBest());

        Returns:
        Example input(s) which causes the algorithm to run in the best case.
        See Also:
        getExampleWorst(), getExampleAverage()

      • getExampleWorst

        For example System.out.println(<Algorithm>.getExampleWorst());

        Returns:
        Example input(s) which causes the algorithm to run in the worst case.
